## Folder Structure (External Only)

This method uses a simple and clear external structure.
Internal logic is not included in this repository.
/  
├── parts/              # External logic units (replaceable)
│   └── example_part/
│       ├── part.php    # External interface
│       └── setting.json
│
├── flow/
│   └── flow.php        # Defines the sequence of parts
│
├── model/
│   └── model.php       # Receives values from parts and passes them to the core
│
├── core/
│   └── core.php        # Internal engine (not included, private to each creator)
│
└── index.php           # Entry point

## Example Use Case (External Only)

1. Select a part (e.g., "post_list")
2. Edit the external settings in setting.json
3. Place the part inside the flow
4. model.php receives the values from the part
5. core.php processes internally (not included in this repository)
6. The final output is rendered on index.php

## Why This Method Exists (External Reason Only)

Modern development often mixes logic and structure, creating complexity.
This method separates them completely:

- Parts = logic (owned by each creator)
- Grammar = structure (shared external rules)
- Core = private internal engine

This separation makes systems stable, replaceable, and easier to build,
especially in the AI era where code generation is common.
